{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/automatically-locking-unlocking-ubuntu-with-computer-vision-using-a-human-face-db35cbe312f7", "time": 1683011862.142911, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/automatically-locking-unlocking-ubuntu-with-computer-vision-using-a-human-face-db35cbe312f7/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Automatically Locking & Unlocking Ubuntu with Computer Vision Using a Human Face!!! | by Bala Venkatesh | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Automatically Locking & Unlocking Ubuntu with Computer Vision Using a Human Face!!!", "description": "Before playing with the code, let us see the libraries that need to be installed on your Ubuntu machine. As a first step, we have to generate training images to train the models. I have created a\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://docs.python.org/3/library/pickle.html", "anchor_text": "pickle library", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNOME_Screensaver", "anchor_text": "gnome shell", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://github.com/balavenkatesh3322/face_unlock", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 14}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/bala-venkatesh-67964247/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/balavenkatesh22", "anchor_text": "Twitter", "paragraph_index": 15}], "all_paragraphs": ["Before playing with the code, let us see the libraries that need to be installed on your Ubuntu machine.", "Below are the three python files that are just enough to achieve this!!!", "As a first step, we have to generate training images to train the models. I have created a python file to generate our face image. When you execute this file, it will ask your name in the command line then the system will create a folder with the given name.", "After that, we need to use the OpenCV library to read our face via webcam and store it in the respective folder, before saving to that folder we should resize our image.", "This will take 50 face images to train the model, you can change the number of image counts as per your requirements.", "This file will read every face image that is generated by face_genrate.py file. Upon completion, we need to pass them into the load_image_file method to get the face location of the images.", "Before training our face model, we should encode our images, so I used the face_encoding method. Also, we should store our names in one array to train with the k-nearest neighbor algorithm.", "Sci-kit learn library is popular for the machine learning algorithm. We have used the KNeighborsClassifier algorithm which is provided by sci-kit learn library.", "Finally, We should save our model file using the pickle library.", "This python file will lock & unlock the ubuntu system based on the trained image. Let\u2019s first capture our face via webcam using the OpenCV library. After using the read method, we can read face images as frames.", "We must detect the face location from the image, hence I\u2019ve used the face_location method. After getting the face location we should pass into the face_encodings method to encode face image to process the next step.", "Before predicting, knn model should be used to find the best matches for the given face. Below is the prediction method to verify the face. It will return the name and top, left, right & bottom variable.", "Use gnome shell command to Lock and Unlock the ubuntu system.", "If the user\u2019s face is unknown or not detected, the system will remain in a locked state.", "That\u2019s it, we have successfully tested the auto-lock & unlock technique of ubuntu using a human face with the help of three python files listed above. You can get the complete source code here", "if you need any help or assistance please connect with me LinkedIn and Twitter.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "I have a passion for understanding technology at a fundamental level and Sharing ideas and code. *